description: This South Cambridgeshire village is located a few miles east of Sandy in a nice rural spot. This walk from the village follows a section of the Clopton Way through the countryside to the nearby Potton Wood. The woods are a nice peaceful place for an easy stroll with lots of wildlife and bluebells in the spring. Please scroll down for the full list of walks near and around Gamlingay. The detailed maps below also show a range of footpaths, bridleways and cycle paths in the area.
